# AI Interviewer Data Cleanup Cron Jobs
# 
# Add these entries to your crontab to automate data cleanup
# Edit with: crontab -e
# View with: crontab -l

# Run data cleanup daily at 2:00 AM
0 2 * * * cd /path/to/ai-interviewer && node scripts/cleanup-data.js >> logs/cleanup.log 2>&1

# Run data cleanup weekly on Sundays at 3:00 AM (more thorough cleanup)
0 3 * * 0 cd /path/to/ai-interviewer && node scripts/cleanup-data.js --policy-file scripts/weekly-policy.json >> logs/weekly-cleanup.log 2>&1

# Run dry-run cleanup every hour during business hours for monitoring
0 9-17 * * 1-5 cd /path/to/ai-interviewer && node scripts/cleanup-data.js --dry-run >> logs/dry-run.log 2>&1

# Alternative: Using npm scripts
# 0 2 * * * cd /path/to/ai-interviewer && npm run cleanup >> logs/cleanup.log 2>&1

# Notes:
# - Replace /path/to/ai-interviewer with the actual path to your project
# - Ensure the logs directory exists: mkdir -p logs
# - Make sure Node.js is in the PATH for the cron user
# - Consider using absolute paths for node and npm commands
# - Test the commands manually before adding to cron
# - Monitor the log files for errors and successful runs